<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="541" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1609,1742]" pageId="11" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,588,1609,1634]" pageId="11" pageNumber="541">Distribution and natural history.</emphasis>
The species is known only from the Central Province of 
<collectingCountry box="[1223,1335,1609,1634]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="11" pageNumber="541">
Sri 
<taxonomicName box="[1262,1335,1609,1634]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanka">Lanka</taxonomicName>
</collectingCountry>
, where it was collected in forest leaf litter at elevations ranging from 
<quantity box="[820,989,1645,1670]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="541" unit="m" value="875.0" valueMax="1000.0" valueMin="750.0">750 to 1000 m</quantity>
.a.s.l.
</paragraph>
